data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles - Relapse
data.tags: Arbor Snowboards,Camber,Product Profiles,Product Video,Snowboarding,Relapse,Arbor
data.description: Before instagrams, there were epigrams; saying such as, “the more things change, the more they stay the same.” And before a variety of hybrid technologies bombarded and confused the common snowboarder, there was classic camber. The Relapse is an ode to our roots; the perfect board for a rider looking for traditional snap, turning and stability in a twin freestyle snowboard. There are those who prefer a straightforward pepperoni pizza when confronted with a supermarket freezer packed with artisanal gluten-free flatbreads; and for those, we provide the Relapse.

data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles - Poparazzi
data.tags: Arbor Snowboards,Arbor,Product Video,Poparazzi,Snowboarding,Product Profiles,Rocker System
data.description: If you’re not looking for the spotlight, you better steer clear of the Poparazzi because you’re gonna be bagging cover shots in no time after stepping foot on this board. The Poparazzi is a medium to soft flex, women’s specific rocker snowboard designed to take you anywhere on the mountain without taking a toll on your wallet. Parabolic reverse camber and Grip Tech make this board exceptionally easy to ride so that you can focus on improving the techniques that will allow you to progress to the next level.

data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles - Foundation
data.tags: Foundation,Arbor,Snowboarding,Arbor Snowboards,Rocker System,Product Video,Product Profiles
data.description: When progression is your top priority, it is crucial that you first start with a solid foundation. An entry-level snowboard with class and style, the Foundation is the perfect board for the rider who is looking to take their snowboarding to the next level. Parabolic reverse camber creates a “catch-free” riding experience for effortless turning and faster learning. The end result? You’ll be on the mountain longer, having more fun, and reaching your goals in no time.

data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles - Formula
data.tags: Rocker System,Arbor,Snowboarding,Arbor Snowboards,Product Profiles,Formula,Product Video
data.description: With the help of the quad-radical equation, we discovered the ultimate Formula for shredding - one part easy to ride, three parts style and two parts affordability. This is the perfect stick to get that bang your buck has been looking for without having to sacrifice style or quality. Built on the System technology offered on our highest end boards and constructed from the same premium materials you’ve come to expect from Arbor, the Formula offers Arbor performance at a fraction of the price.

data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles- Element Premium
data.tags: Element Premium,Arbor,Rocker System,Arbor Snowboards,Product Video,Snowboarding,Element,Product Profiles
data.description: The board that started it all, The Element has been the cornerstone of our line for the past 20 years. With all-mountain proficiency, clean styling, and a focus on craftsmanship, this quintessential Arbor snowboard speaks to our core values and is sure to remain a classic for years to come. The Element is available in an upgraded version with a cleaner graphic and premium Palisander topsheet, or standard black, hand-dyed ash topsheet.

data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles - Element Mini
data.tags: Mini System,Snowboarding,Product Profiles,Product Video,Arbor Snowboards,Kids Snowboard,Arbor,Rocker System,Youth,Element Mini
data.description: Small but mighty, the Element Mini delivers the same technology and styling of our cornerstone snowboard in a scaled down version for younger rippers. We’ve built this youth model on our award winning Rocker System, to increase the ease of learning that comes with a reverse camber platform. More catch free edging and increased board control will have junior progressing so fast, you might not be able to keep up.

data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles - Zygote Twin
data.tags: Snowboard,Arbor Snowboards,Arbor,Snowboarding,Product Video,Camber System,Zygote Twin,Product Profile,Non-Symmetrical Twin
data.description: The Zygote Twin is a non-symmetrical twin, a fusion of true-twin on-snow geometry with distinct tip and tail outlines that pay homage to the shaping and art traditions of early skate and snow design. While dissimilar in shape, the tip and tail share identical widths, heights and lengths, creating a symmetrical twin ride designed for true-cambered, freestyle snowboarding.

data.tags: Snowboarding,Product Video,Arbor,Rocker System,Arbor Snowboards,Whiskey,Snowboard,Product Profile
data.description: Here at Arbor, we appreciate a good whiskey. When distilling this fine corduroy crushing elixir, we work hard to elicit notes of all-mountain versatility and cross terrain mobility. Whether you prefer it on the rocks, in a straight shot down the steeps or barreling through the trees, we are confident that your palate will be pleased with the broad scope of performance that only the Whiskey can provide.

data.title: Arbor Snowboards :: 2016 Product Profiles - Swoon Rocker
data.tags: Rocker System,Arbor Snowboards,Snowboarding,Arbor,Product Video,Swoon Rocker,Product Profiles
data.description: A women’s specific all-mountain snowboard, the Swoon is built on a mountain-twin shape with a medium flex. Responsive pop and powerful edge control make the Swoon the perfect board for women who don’t let ski area boundaries limit their riding. More responsive than the Cadence, The Swoon offers increased stability at higher speeds for the more advanced rider. We have expanded the Swoon offering to include both System Rocker and System Camber versions.
